Workflow to Add Ecommerce Data to the Example OmniScript

Google Tag Manager Ecommerce requires specific kinds of data. You must add this data to the Messaging Framework OmniScript properties. Then when the OmniScript runs, it sends this data to Google Analytics.

The example OmniScript and FlexCard communicate with Google Analytics 4 by using the Google Tag Manager Ecommerce APIs.

For simplicity, the example OmniScript uses hard-coded data.

Add Google Tag Manager Data to the Example OmniScript Steps:

The Messaging Framework of each step stores the product data thatâ€™s sent to Google Analytics Ecommerce and the Google Tag Manager.

After you add Google Tag Manager data, return to the parent workflow and perform the Workflow to Create an External Tracking Configuration and Event Types.
